Key Match Events: Babar Azam scored 75 runs off 42 balls with a strike rate of 178.57.
Shaheen Afridi took 3 wickets for 14 runs with an economy rate of 3.5.
Shaheen Afridi was named Man of the Match.
Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan had a 139-run partnership.
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam praised the Irish batters for their performance in the first half and mentioned the importance of his bowlers taking wickets to put pressure.
Lorcan Tucker expressed pride in leading the team and satisfaction with the bowlers' performance despite tough conditions.
Shaheen Afridi highlighted the importance of hitting good lines and lengths and preparing the team for the World Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Pakistan chased down the target, scoring 181/4 in 17 overs.
